title:          "Protecting the ego: Motivated information selection and updating"
date:           2022-01-01 00:00:00 +0100
selected:       true

pub:            "European Economic Review"
pub_date:       "2022"

abstract: >-
  This paper studies how individuals selectively acquire and update information
  to protect their ego. Using experimental evidence, it shows that agents tend to
  avoid or downweight unfavorable information, leading to biased belief updating
  with implications for decision-making and welfare.

